They discovered that the Sun operates based on the same basic principles as other stars: it was discovered that the activity of all the stars in the system is driven by their luminosity, rotation, and nothing else.
To determine a star's Rossby number, which is related to the plasma flow, luminosity and rotation are taken into account together.
The smaller the Rossby number, the less active the star is in terms of polarity reversals of the magnetic field.
