The effect the team was looking for would be caused by tidal forces between the galaxy's dark matter and the Milky Way's dark matter.
Just as the Moon pulls on the Earth and causes tides, the Milky Way also exerts gravitational pull on the Sagittarius Galaxy.
The scientists concluded that dark matter acts on other dark matter in the same way as normal matter.
This theory suggests that most dark matter is found in a kind of halo around a galaxy and is made up of many small particles.
